.chapter(data-title='SMS API Python Quickstart')
  .step(data-title='Welcome!', data-file='../README.MD')
    h2 Welcome to SMS API Python Quickstart

    p This is a quickstart tutorial to teach users to use RingCentral SMS API.

  .step(data-title='Environment Variables', data-file='../README')
    :markdown
      ### Clone the project
      Clone the project from GitHub and install RingCentral SDK and dependencies.

  .step(data-title='Environment Variables', data-file='../dotenv')
    :markdown
      ## Environment Variables

      The first file we'll look at is `.env.sample`. This contains all the environment variables we used in this tutorial. You need to follow its sample to create `.env` file which contains real RingCentral credentials.

      Most of the environment variables are quite self-explanatory except the last one: `RINGCENTRAL_RECEIVER`. It means the number to receive SMS. You can set it to your own mobile phone number so that you can confirm the receipt of SMS.

